## Presenting the Past: Exploring the American Archive of Public Broadcasting Podcast 

The American Archive of Public Broadcasting (AAPB) is a collaboration between the Library of Congress and WGBH Educational Foundation to coordinate a national effort to digitally preserve and make accessible historically significant public radio and television programs created over the past 70+ year. More than [130 participating](https://americanarchive.org/participating-orgs) stations and original producers have shared their collection metadata and digitized news casts, raw interviews, documentaries, cultural programs, and more with the AAPB, making seven decades of public broadcasting searchable and accessible to the public. 

Hosted by Christine Becker Members of AAPB's [Scholar Advisory Committee](https://americanarchive.org/about-the-american-archive/advisory-committees) (SAC) are guests an audio series with that will explore the breadth and depth of the archive. Hosted by Christine Becker, __ Aca-Media co-host and co-producer each interview consist of a short conversation about content in the AAPB.

